<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="480" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,222,823]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,222,247]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. In the group III key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier" box="[607,810,222,247]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1964) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part II. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Aphiochaeta. Studia Entomologica, 7, 257 - 416." type="journal article" year="1964">
Borgmeier (
<number box="[741,802,222,247]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[821,964,223,246]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steptoeae">
<emphasis box="[821,964,223,246]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. steptoeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys to couplet 
<number box="[1147,1175,223,247]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" value="13.0">13</number>
where it can readily be distinguished from both 
<taxonomicName authority="Brues" authorityName="Brues" box="[427,629,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scopalis">
<emphasis box="[427,556,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. scopalis</emphasis>
Brues
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Borgmeier." authorityName="Borgmeier." box="[684,927,258,283]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="renata">
<emphasis box="[684,795,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. renata</emphasis>
Borgmeier.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[933,1077,259,282]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steptoeae">
<emphasis box="[933,1077,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. steptoeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the forceps-like epandrial process and strong anipisternal bristle of 
<taxonomicName box="[621,752,294,318]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scopalis">
<emphasis box="[621,752,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. scopalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[768,913,295,318]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steptoeae">
<emphasis box="[768,913,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. steptoeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is differentiated easily from 
<taxonomicName box="[1245,1356,295,318]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="renata">
<emphasis box="[1245,1356,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. renata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the structure of the genitalia. In 
<taxonomicName box="[478,590,331,354]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="renata">
<emphasis box="[478,590,331,354]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. renata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the epandrium has a triangular notch near the rear margin and numerous stout bristles near the lower margin of the epandrium; 
<taxonomicName box="[754,896,367,390]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steptoeae">
<emphasis box="[754,896,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. steptoeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks such a notch and has few bristles arranged in a more-or-less vertical row on the epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[700,783,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 87 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,255,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[150,1436,241,1829]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 87 – 92. Male genitalia, left lateral. 87. Megaselia rodriguezorum. 88. Megaselia sacatelensis. 89. Megaselia seaverorum. 90. Megaselia sidneyae. 91. Megaselia steptoeae. 92. Megaselia wiegmanae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242988/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">
Fig. 
<number box="[752,783,403,427]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" value="91.0">91</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
